Gertrude Coghlan https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gertrude_Coghlan 0 Gertrude Coghlan (February 1, 1876 – September 11, 1952) was an English actress born in Hertfordshire, England. She is known for her role in the play The Travelling Salesman and other roles in silent cinema as: The Royal Box (1914), The Countess and the Burglar (1914) and Her Ladyship (1914).She was Charles Francis Coghlan's daughter and older sister of Charles F. Coghlan also a stage actor and she was married to Augustus Pitou a theatrical producer. She died on September 11, 1952 in Bayside, New York City.
